  "prompt": "How can I get YouTube comments?",
  "response": "There are several methods to retrieve YouTube comments, including using the official YouTube API, third-party software, or browser extensions. Here are a few ways:\n\n### Method 1: Using YouTube API\n\n1. **Set Up the API Access:**\n   - Go to the [Google Developer Console](https://console.developers.google.com/).\n   - Create a new project.\n   - Enable the YouTube Data API v3 for your project.\n   - Create credentials (API key).\n\n2. **Using Python:**\n   ```python\n   import googleapiclient.discovery\n\n   def get_youtube_comments(video_id, api_key):\n       # Build the API client\n       youtube = googleapiclient.discovery.build('youtube', 'v3', developerKey=api_key)\n\n       # Make the request\n       request = youtube.commentThreads().list(\n           part=\"snippet\",\n           videoId=video_id,\n           maxResults=100\n       )\n       response = request.execute()\n       \n       comments = []\n       for item in response['items']:\n           comment = item['snippet']['topLevelComment']['snippet']['textOriginal']\n           comments.append(comment)\n\n       return comments\n\n   API_KEY = 'YOUR_API_KEY'\n   VIDEO_ID = 'YOUR_VIDEO_ID'\n\n   comments = get_youtube_comments(VIDEO_ID, API_KEY)\n   for comment in comments:\n       print(comment)\n   ```\n   Replace `YOUR_API_KEY` and `YOUR_VIDEO_ID` with your actual API key and video ID.\n\n### Method 2: Browser Extension\n\n1. **Download a YouTube comment extraction extension**: \n   - Extensions like \"YouTube Comment Extractor\" are available for browsers like Chrome.\n   \n2. **Use the extension**: \n   - Follow the extension\u2019s instructions on how to extract comments from a specific video.\n\n### Method 3: Third-Party Software\n\n1. **Use software tools**:\n   - Tools like `TubeKit`, `Octoparse`, and `WebHarvy` can scrape YouTube comments.\n   - They usually have easy-to-follow interfaces.\n\n### Method 4: Directly from YouTube\n\n1. **Manually collecting data**:\n   - Open the YouTube video.\n   - Scroll through the comments section.\n   - Copy and paste the comments manually, which is time-consuming but does not require any technical setup.\n\nAlways ensure you comply with YouTube\u2019s terms of service and privacy policies when collecting and using comment data.",
